In[29]:
#Transformation of the data Begins

tmpdf=df
tmpdf['life_stage'] = tmpdf['age'].apply(lambda x: 'Kiddo' if x <13 else ('Teen' if x< 20 else 'Adult'))

def categorize_health_status(row):
    if row['sleep_hours'] > 5.0 and row['daily_steps'] > 3000 and row['water_intake_l'] > 2.0:
        return 'Healthy'
    else:
        return 'Unhealthy'
tmpdf['Category'] = tmpdf.apply(categorize_health_status, axis=1)
tmpdf.sample(10)

In[36]:
vsdf = tmpdf.copy()

# Check correlations quickly
corr = vsdf.corr(numeric_only=True)
print(corr[["resting_hr", "bmi", "disease_risk"]].sort_values(by="resting_hr", ascending=False))

# 1 Daily Steps vs Resting Heart Rate
plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
sns.scatterplot(data=vsdf, x="daily_steps", y="resting_hr", alpha=0.4)
sns.regplot(data=vsdf, x="daily_steps", y="resting_hr", scatter=False, color="green", label="Trend")
plt.title("More Daily Steps  Lower Resting Heart Rate", fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel("Daily Steps")
plt.ylabel("Resting Heart Rate (bpm)")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
plt.show()

# 2 Calories Consumed vs BMI
plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
sns.scatterplot(data=vsdf, x="calories_consumed", y="bmi", alpha=0.4)
sns.regplot(data=vsdf, x="calories_consumed", y="bmi", scatter=False, color="red", label="Trend")
plt.title("Higher Calorie Intake  Higher BMI", fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel("Calories Consumed")
plt.ylabel("BMI")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
plt.show()

# 3 Cholesterol by Disease Risk (Boxplot)
plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
sns.boxplot(data=vsdf, x="disease_risk", y="cholesterol", palette="Set2")
plt.title("Higher Cholesterol Levels Associated with Higher Disease Risk", fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel("Disease Risk (0 = Low, 1 = High)")
plt.ylabel("Cholesterol (mg/dL)")
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
plt.show()

# 4 Sleep Hours vs Resting HR (optional if correlation > 0.2)
plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
sns.scatterplot(data=vsdf, x="sleep_hours", y="resting_hr", alpha=0.4)
sns.regplot(data=vsdf, x="sleep_hours", y="resting_hr", scatter=False, color="blue", label="Trend")
plt.title("More Sleep  Slightly Lower Resting Heart Rate", fontsize=15)
plt.xlabel("Sleep Hours")
plt.ylabel("Resting Heart Rate (bpm)")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)
plt.show()
